CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 11, 1961, p. 2, reads: "Candidates Work Hard in Victory Quest - Plotting Strategy - Plotting Democratic strategy, Tuesday in the Third and Fourth Districts, 13th Ward, were, left to right: Committeeman Wendell Allen, Lee Washington, who won the constable's post; Ward Chairman Linn Washington, Lee's brother, and Gerald Fox, ward secretary. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Wendell Allen, Lee Washington, Linn Washington, and Gerald Fox standing outside of polling place
